      "stimulus_html": "",
      "stem_html": "<p>The following molecular model is a representation of <i>para</i>-aminobenzoic acid (PABA), the active ingredient in many sunscreens. Indicate the positions of the multiple bonds, and draw a skeletal structure (black = C, red = O, blue = N, gray = H).</p>\n<img class=\"scaled-down\" src=\"https://exercises.openstax.org/rails/active_storage/blobs/proxy/eyJfcmFpbHMiOnsibWVzc2FnZSI6IkJBaHBBcFVVIiwiZXhwIjpudWxsLCJwdXIiOiJibG9iX2lkIn19--05c964f4c855c165cfa3c8161a6db3f5ab637449/OChem_01_12_007.jpg\" alt=\"The ball and stick model of para-aminobenzoic acid abbreviated as PABA.\">",
